RankEvolve is an AI-driven workflow for evolving Meta's ranking models. It follows a structured methodology:

**Phase 0 — Setup**: Set the workflow target path (`workflow_target_path`) and choose an evolution strategy.

**Phase 1 — Codebase Investigation**: Analyze the target codebase to understand its architecture, data flow, model structure, and extension points. Produces structured documentation of findings.

**Phase 2 — Research & Proposal**: Break down the research goal into sub-queries, execute parallel deep research streams, generate architecture proposals, and synthesize them into a unified design.

**Phase 3 — Implementation, Experiment & Analysis**: Plan and implement the proposed changes, run experiments to validate, and analyze results to identify bottlenecks and improvement opportunities.

**Phase 4 — Summary & Evolve**: Summarize all experiment results and decide whether to continue another research-proposal-experiment cycle. If yes, loop back to Phase 2 with refined goals based on findings.
